OL,6,F"There were a lot of tears and my wife
OL,7,FSarah was in bits when he ran on to
OL,8,Fthe pitch and I tried to be a big man,
OL,9,FI suppose.
OL,11,F"I tried to hold it together but I
OL,12,Fcried on my own. I took myself into
OL,13,Fone of the changing rooms and I had a
OL,14,Flittle cry.
OL,16,F"It was emotional but I was so proud
OL,17,Fof him, to come back after 18 months
OL,18,Fand to run on that pitch and be
OL,19,Fabsolutely fearless."
