OL,6,FReflecting on his decision to play
OL,7,Frugby again, Dylan says: "I wanted to
OL,8,Fprove a point that I could come back
OL,9,Fand be the same player I was.
OL,11,F"I wanted to prove to everyone that
OL,12,Fsimply an injury doesn't have to stop
OL,13,Fyou playing sport."
OL,15,FHad he never kicked a rugby ball
OL,16,Fagain, nobody would have held it
OL,17,Fagainst him.
OL,19,FBut he's moving forward, refusing to
OL,20,Flet the past define his future.
